DB RDL 10 full reps 10 bottom range

node.text:
-
CHOC CARAMEL OXYWHEY😱🍫🎉
-
I am SO excited to finally announce my very own protein flavour in collaboration with @ehplabs. You all know that I’ve been using Oxywhey for years now and it has been my ULTIMATE compliance buddy throughout every stage of my fitness journey, since the very beginning 😍.
-
From hitting my sweet tooth during WBFF World Championships preparation when living the calorie deficit life, to fuelling my booty gains when in a surplus🍑... To have my own flavour is an absolute dream come true💫!
-
What I’ve learned over the years is that the key to success on your health and fitness journey is to be prepared and not to deprive. Having Oxywhey has allowed me to stay complaint to my goals while not missing out on living my best life (hellooo, protein oats every morning!). Oxywhey has:
-
💫25g protein per serve.
💫Super probiotics (gut health, hair & skin).
💫B Vitamins (vitality and energy).
💫Alkalising vitamins and minerals for optimal health.
💫100% pure, lean, non-GMO whey protein.
💫All flavours are 100% natural.
-
Head to the LINK IN MY BIO to sign up to the exclusive mailing list to be the first to know when you can get your hands on my EHP CHOC CARAMEL Oxywhey 😋🍫
-
Link in my bio @laurensimpson

node.text:
.
You have changed my life. You have made me better. You have made me believe in myself. I appreciate YOU.
.
I know not every day is easy for you, so my favourite thing in the world is seeing you laugh and smile...this video makes me a little 🥺🥺🥺.
.
I am forever grateful we crossed paths and the universe brought us together. What we have is so special & I couldn’t imagine doing life without you.
.
I love you. @coachmarkcarroll

LSF GIRLS GET RESULTS. Meet @yoiamkosjo She won the Bikini X Strong challenge last year 🥳💓

This is her 8 week transformation. 😍If you swipe on this post you will see her result from 2x challenges.

Jola is a Polish girl living in the UK! 🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧She trains from HOME with minimal equipment.

Please never underestimate the power of home training & the transformation you can achieve! The programs are written with strategies to help push you and find ways to effectively challenge your muscles when you can’t necessarily increase weight.👏🏼

THIS IS PROOF LSF HOME PROGRAMS WORK!

In the LSF app 📲you can switch between HOME & GYM anytime. For home training all you need are dumbbells & a booty band.

On this challenge Jola increased her calories to BUILD. She wanted to focus on building her glutes more, spending time out of a calorie deficit & getting stronger. On my challenges you can focus on shredding or increasing calories to build. You can go through phases all year with LSF - fat loss and then building. 💪🏼

BIKINI X STRONG 8 week challenge 2021 intake in now open!

If you sign up now you get instant access to the LSF APP for the ‘pre season’ program - the meal plan, hundreds of recipes . ⭐️

If you haven’t joined us…what are you waiting for? ⏰ GO QUEENS!

Hit the link in my bio  @LAURENSIMPSON

node.text:
BIKINI STRONG CHALLENGE SAMPLE WORKOUT 💪🏼💜🔥

Link in my bio to join @laurensimpson

My new 8 week challenge now has 2 different training levels: beginner / intermediate and ‘Train like Loz’ Advanced. 
Both levels have HOME + GYM versions.

Here is a sample workout from the Advanced  program. This is based EXACTLY off my own training. Experience an 8 week phase alongside me. I am SO EXCITED for this.🥺🙋🏼‍♀️🥳

You girls know I love to get strong, so this program is built around the compound lifts like squats, deadlift, hip thrust, presses and pulls - however it still will have the LS style with my more fancy variations and methods. How you see me training on the daily. You will get to really hit some good strength goals by the end of the 8 weeks when the reps are lower and you can increase those weights! 💪🏼

🔥ADVANCED PROGRAM is 5 days per week (6th optional day).
3x Lower body days
2x Upper body days
Optional cardio/abs day
1 hour workouts + advanced finishers!
🥵🔥

WORKOUT:

CONCENTRIC FOCUSED HIP THRUST (3 second concentric + pause at the top)
TRAP BAR RDL
FEET HIGH LEG PRESS (Final set using rest/pause method)
BACK EXTENSION
LEG EXTENSION
CABLE KICKBACK

+ an advanced finisher! 😏😏

BIKINI STRONG 8 WEEK CHALLENGE SIGN UPS OPEN!⭐️

Sign up now & get immediate access to the LSF APP! We are prepping you in advance with a bonus FREE program in the lead up.

THIS CHALLENGE IS GOING TO BE BIG!
Official start: 16 August.
🥳🥳🥳

SO, WHO’S IN?

Link in my bio to secure your spot @laurensimpson

node.text:
ME THEN VS ME NOW

2015: Even though I look lean - this is what you don’t see👇🏼

🚫Severely under eating. Basically starving myself of nutrients my body needed to thrive. I went through vigorous cycles of extreme calorie restriction and then binging.
🚫 Avoided social outings because I couldn’t track my food properly.
🚫I exercised purely to burn calories. I only wanted to do cardio at the beginning because I was scared of the weights room.
🚫I was the least confident in myself I had even been in my life - despite being at my lowest weight. I was so insecure.
🚫I felt like I was never good enough. 

2021: NOW...

🦋I eat to fuel my body & have developed a healthy relationship with food.
🦋I lift HEAVY AF and want to be strong.
🦋I am more confident in myself, and know my value and worth.

My progress is a result of years of consistency and hard work. It’s never perfect - but I keep going. I don’t give up.🔥

You have the power to step into the GIRL you are designed to be. The power is in your hands… you just have to decide you truly want it. 💪🏼

BIKINI X STRONG 💜💪🏼8 WEEK CHALLENGE 😱 Our most iconic challenge is BACK..BIGGER & BETTER!💥
Link in my bio to join now @laurensimpson

This challenge encompasses everything I am about as a person, coach & brand.

✨STRONG CONFIDENT FEMALES. 👑✨

This is THE challenge to give you the full experience to train exactly like me. I’m giving you the secrets of a World Bikini Champion with your food, training & mindset to get your own TRANSFORMATION.✨

There is so much NEW for this challenge!!!🤩

💪🏼8 week training programs. 2 experience level options for our GYM and HOME programs - Beginner/ Intermediate + ‘TRAIN LIKE LOZ’ Advanced.

➡️Beginner/Intermediate: 4 days per week (2 optional days) Workouts approx 45 minutes. Gain confidence with your training & watch how fast you will progress!

➡️’TRAIN LIKE LOZ’ Advanced: 5 days per week (6th optional day)
1 hour workouts + advanced finishers.
Focus on getting stronger on the main lifts!
Both home + gym programs are based off my own EXACT training.

So many new exercises & variations added to these challenges programs. LEVEL UP 💪🏼

🍎You will get a custom meal plan + macros/calories. 50+ new meals added to the extensive database (750+), New recipes added + brand new cooking videos added to the LSF app weekly!!!!👏🏼👏🏼

🥳‘PRE-SEASON’ CHALLENGE PROGRAM!! BRAND NEW for LSF! Sign up now and get immediate access to the LSF APP! We are prepping you in advance. You will have a bonus program to start now in the lead up!!

📲 BRAND NEW APP DESIGN! Sleek new look and feel. Loving the new vibe for your home for the next 8 weeks. ✨ 

🔥I’ve been able to team up with EHPLABS again to offer you HUGE bundle savings with supplements + challenge!

The challenge also includes all the other incredible benefits such as our exclusive Facebook community, live chats with me, educational videos content, check ins + MORE.

Official start: 16 August.
⁠
💜Become the strongest, sexiest most confident version of yourself 💫. It’s time to build YOUR best bikini body 🔥

SIGN UPS NOW OPEN 🗓. LINK IN BIO to secure your spot👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼 @laurensimpson 

SO WHO’S IN? TAG YOUR GIRLS!

ANY QUESTIONS? Drop them below

FIX YOUR FORM: PUSH UPS ❌✅

PLEASE SAVE + RE-SHARE 🙏🏼🙏🏼

Push ups are a VERY common exercise. Its  body weight only and can be done in some variation regardless of your fitness experience level.

As a coach, I do see a lot of people struggle with them…and a lot of the time I think it’s because they aren’t actually sure what a proper push up should look like!

Here are some common issues and then how it’s corrected.

COMMON MISTAKES

❌HEAD LEADING THE MOVEMENT
❌HANDS TOO FAR FORWARD. When you are in position they should be directly under your shoulders.
❌HIPS TOO HIGH/TOO LOW. This puts unnecessary strain on your lower back. You aren’t using your core here to stabilise your body.
❌HANDS TOO WIDE. This limits your range of motion.
❌ELBOWS FLARED. Elbows should not be pointing directly out to the sides. This is putting strain on your shoulders and not putting your chest in proper alignment to work the muscles you want to be!

FORM TIPS:

✅ELBOWS TUCKED IN SLIGHTLY - AT A 45 DEGREE ANGLE
✅HINGE FROM KNEES (NOT HIPS)
✅HANDS SLIGHTLY WIDER THAN SHOULDER-WIDTH APART.
✅HEAD IN LINE WITH BODY. Maintain alignment with your spine.
✅CORE ENGAGED
✅HIPS DOWN

From a kneeling push up - you can progress to doing them up on your toes.🏆

How many can you do?

I hope this was helpful. ❤️ LET ME KNOW! 🙏🏼

P.s. 1 day to go until the next 8 week challenge will be announced! 🥳

node.text:
GYM HACK: NO BACK EXTENSION MACHINE? TRY THIS!💡💥🤯

I’ve posted this set up hack previously but it was the first time for me doing it at home so thought I’d film and share again!! 👏🏼

Back extensions are one of my favourite for glutes! If your gym doesn’t have the machine try this simple set up using a squat rack, plates & bar pad.

The plates behind your feet will ensure you don’t slip. The pad on the bar will help cushion your hips.

Tip: when doing back extension focus on driving your hips back as you lower down. Initiate the movement from your hips and push your butt back. You should feel this deep in your glute-ham tie in area.

Please let me know if this hack was helpful! ❤️

P.s. 1 day to go until the next 8 week challenge intake is announced 🥳🥳
@laurensimpsonfitness

node.text:
UNDERRATED COACHING CUES 🎯🔥 Changing the game with your technique! 💡

When you gain more confidence in the gym and movements become more like second nature, there are less cues you feel you need to focus on. I usually pick just 1 or 2 each set.

Think of cues like your checklist. 📝

Here are some of my absolute favourites:

⭐️PUSH THE THE FLOOR AWAY or ‘leg press the floor away’. 

With a deadlift often we think about pulling the weight but if you think about ‘pushing’ the floor away from the starting position you create more force output from your lower body. Your legs are so powerful...so use them!!!
Tension from the ground up!

⭐️DRIVE ELBOWS DOWN TO FLOOR.

Pull yourself up (body to bar) by imagining you are driving your elbows down to the floor. Keep your elbows close to your body and not flared out wide. 

⭐️ROW DUMBBELL TO HIP

Lead the dumbbell with your elbow pulling it back to your hip. Keep your elbow close to your side and torso relatively still. You don’t want to be pulling up to your chest. Bring it back to your hip.

⭐️DRAW BELLY BUTTON TO SPINE & ‘DOUBLE CRUNCH’

Belly button to spine is ensuring your core is engaged and tight. To crunch, you should first initiate the movement with your lower abs tucking under and then rolling your spine from there - kinda like a ‘double crunch’.

These have all been absolute game changers for me! I hope they help you too 🤓🎯

P.s. 2 DAYS TO GO UNTIL THE NEXT 8 WEEK CHALLENGE INTAKE IS ANNOUNCED! 🥳
This is going to be big 😏💜 @laurensimpsonfitness

node.text:
OVERATE THIS WEEKEND? 🍪🍫🍿Did you have a high calorie meal or untracked meal on the weekend and now instantly scared of weight gain?
 
I used to be terrified to eat out or eat an off plan meal because I thought I’d wake up 10kg heavier.

💡TRUTH IS: When you do overeat, you may notice some initial temporary changes to your body. This could be bloating, puffiness, water retention etc…it’s just your bodies natural response to perhaps different types of foods you had consumed and also the extra energy it’s now digesting. As a result - yes your weight may temporarily fluctuate.

Significant fat gain doesn’t just happen over night. 1 untracked meal doesn’t make you fat…just like 1 healthy meal doesn’t make you shredded. Eating in a calorie surplus  consistently is what leads to fat gain.‼️

If you are waking up on a Monday morning feeling bloated and puffy after your weekends food /drink - please be kind to yourself. You are not a failure. It’s a new day and you can always get back to your normal routine of meals and I promise after a couple of days you will feel better!

Get your body moving. Get back to your usual meals. Wear your  favourite comfortable clothes.

There is so much more to life than restricting calories, being anxious about enjoying your favourite foods out with loved ones and punishing yourself as a result.

Be kind to yourself on this Monday honeys 💕✨

Outfit: @bombshellsportswear

SHOULDERS + ABS💪🏼🥵

HIT SAVE + TAG your gym bestie. ✨

I haven’t been posting as many full workouts anymore so take advantage of it when I do. 🙏🏼

This workout is primarily shoulders with a little abs at the end. Remember - if you do want to build and grow your shoulders then you need to train them with frequency, intensity and made sure your exercise selection covers your front, medial and rear delts for that ‘capped’ look.

A1) DB SHOULDER PRESS 3x 10 paused. The pause is at the bottom range here where the exercise is hardest.

A2) LATERAL RAISE 3x 10 paused. The pause is at the top range as that’s where your delts are under the most tension and it’s hardest. I’m doing these seated which also makes the exercise harder as there isn’t any momentum or movement from your legs to assist.

A3) AROUND THE WORLD. 3x 12.

B) Y RAISE 3x 12

C) REAR DELT MACHINE 3x 15. With this exercise - more range of motion is not best! Once your rear delt has fully contracted - anything past this is just going to engage your upper back. Take your arms out directly to the sides & stay within your rear delts active range. 

D1) Hanging alt knee raises 3x 12
D2) Cable crunch 3x 15

‼️Are you ready to start getting results with me as your trainer?

My in app programs SHRED, BIKINI BUILD + POWER BOOTY are available to start NOW. Whether you train from HOME or GYM - I got you covered. Includes your nutrition + workouts. ✨

Click the link in my bio to join. @laurensimpson

node.text:
No food is ‘bad’….. 

Give yourself permission to eat food without fear, guilt or self judgement. Shame and stress are feelings we shouldn’t link with food. 🙏🏼

When you stop completely restricting yourself and actually allow yourself to eat foods you love and enjoy in moderation…you actually don’t crave them or have the urgency to overeat them.
 
Yes - there are some foods that are more nutrient dense than others.

Yes - there are some foods that will be easier on your digestive system, keep you feeling more satiated or just make you feel a whole lot better.

But this doesn’t mean you have to completely cut food groups, starve yourself or eat just chicken and broccoli. 🙅🏼‍♀️

It’s about balance.✅✅✅

Food is not just macros or calories…
Food shouldn’t just be looked at as a numbers game.

Shift your mindset from living with guilt and restriction - too thriving and living life to the fullest.🙏🏼🙋🏼‍♀️❤️
